The paper discusses the use of Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) Neural Networks for wind power prediction, which is a common application of machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of weather forecast data, which falls under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the potential impact of wind power prediction on power grid stability, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SD (Systems and Control). Furthermore, the paper involves the use of renewable energy sources, which falls under the sub-category of cs.NE (Networking and Internet Architecture). Finally, the paper involves the use of data analysis and modeling techniques, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
